[![Winter is coming to Gaza, where some 100,000 people have been left
homeless. On Twitter, @NourAlghussain says: "winter is on the doors here .and
Gaza is still besieged >there's no materials to rebuild these houses
#BreakGazaSiege" ](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2014/10/ByjjFzHCEAAXMhR.jpg)](https://twitter.com/NourAlGhussein/status/515911848042844160)

加薩的冬天即將到來，然而卻有約十萬人無家可歸。[@NourAlghussein
](https://twitter.com/NourAlGhussein/status/515911848042844160)在推特上說：「冬天就要來了，加薩依然遭到包圍，沒有可供重建的物資。#解除包圍加薩」

在[今年夏天的戰爭](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2014_Israel%E2%80%93Gaza_conflict)中遭到[重度破壞](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/gaza-
civilian-death-toll-mounts-in-israeli-offensive/)後，數千加薩民眾已沒有足夠的資源抵禦寒冬。

2014
年十月聯合國人道事務協調室（OCHA）[報告](http://www.ochaopt.org/documents/ocha_opt_protection_of_civilians_weekly_report_2014_10_17_english.pdf)指出，估計約有兩萬戶房屋被毀，十萬人流離失所，難民或和寄宿家庭同住，或是住在像學校一類的團體中心。

秋天的第一場雨引起推特上對難民未來的擔憂：

> If You Want To See How People In
> [#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash) Spend The Winter This
> Year Here Is A Sample For You Sir/Madam
> …[#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash)
> [#Winter](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Winter?src=hash)
> [pic.twitter.com/DFvnoXGcc0](http://t.co/DFvnoXGcc0)
>
> — Salah AlQady (@salah_alqady) [October 19,
> 2014](https://twitter.com/salah_alqady/status/523954633224757248)

> 想看看加薩人民今年將如何過冬的話，這裡有範例：pic.twitter.com/DFvnoXGcc0
>
> — Salah AlQady (@salah_alqady) 2014 年十月十九日

> Heavy rains in [#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash). First
> winter storm to hit since the end of war, with thousands of families
> displaced or living in damaged homes
>
> — Fares Akram (@faresakram) [October 19,
> 2014](https://twitter.com/faresakram/status/523734809026527232)

> 加薩大雨中。戰後第一場冬季暴風雨，數千戶人家流離失所或只能住在破損的房子。
>
> — Fares Akram (@faresakram) 2014 年十月十九日

加薩部落格作者 Omar Ghraieb寫道：

> It hasnt stopped raining since the morning & I havent stopped praying &
> thinking about displaced & homeless people here & everywhere.
> [#Gaza](https://twitter.com/hashtag/Gaza?src=hash)
>
> — Omar Ghraieb (@Omar_Gaza) [October 19,
> 2014](https://twitter.com/Omar_Gaza/status/523790513254576128)

> 今天早上開始雨下個不停，我也不停為各處無家可歸的人們祈禱。
>
> — Omar Ghraieb (@Omar_Gaza) 2014 年十月十九日

